Name.BusinessNameLine1: JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER OF GREATER ROCH

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: THE MISSION OF THE JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER OF GREATER ROCHESTER IS TO STRENGTHEN JEWISH IDENTITY AND PROMOTE JEWISH CONTINUITY IN AN ENVIRONMENT THAT PROVIDES OPPORTUNITIES FOR MEANINGFUL CULTURAL ENRICHMENT, PHYSICAL WELL-BEING, SOCIAL, EDUCATIONAL AND RECREATIONAL EXPERIENCES FOR INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES. WE WELCOME PEOPLE OF ALL FAITHS, RACES, ABILITIES, AGES AND INCOMES. NO ONE IS TURNED AWAY FOR INABILITY TO PAY. OUR STRENGTH IS IN THE PEOPLE WE BRING TOGETHER. WE ARE NOT A RELIGIOUS ORGANIZATION; HOWEVER WE OFFER JEWISH CULTURAL PROGRAMMING TO THE GREATER ROCHESTER JEWISH COMMUNITY IN ADDITION TO OUR HUMAN SERVICES MISSION. THE JCC OF ROCHESTER IS THE LARGEST NOT-FOR-PROFIT HUMAN SERVICE ORGANIZATION IN THE BRIGHTON-HENRIETTA-PITTSFORD AREA OF GREATER ROCHESTER. LAST YEAR THE JCC SERVED 13,366 NON DUPLICATED, ACTIVE MEMBERS. WE PROVIDE 11% OF OUR MEMBERSHIP UNITS WITH MORE THAN $200,000 IN MEMBERSHIP SCHOLARSHIP ASSISTANCE. WE PROVIDE ANOTHER $50,000 IN CAMP SCHOLARSHIPS.
IRS990.MissionDescription: THE JCC OF GREATER ROCHESTER PROVIDES A COMPREHENSIVE RANGE OF SERVICES THAT PROVIDE FOR THE CULTURAL ENRICHMENT, PHYSICAL WELL-BEING, SOCIAL, EDUCATIONAL AND RECREATIONAL EXPERIENCES FOR INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES.
IRS990.Description: AS A HEALTH, WELLNESS AND PHYSICAL FITNESS FACILITY THE JCC OF GREATER ROCHESTER IS THE SECOND LARGEST FITNESS FACILITY IN THE GREATER ROCHESTER AREA RANKED BY THE NUMBER OF MEMBERS. THE 155,000 SQUARE FOOT FACILITY HOUSES AN OLYMPIC-SIZED INDOOR SWIMMING POOL; INDOOR TRACK; FULL GYMNASIUM; YOUTH PLAY GYM FOR CHILDREN 2 TO 10; VIRTUAL GYM AND CARDIO ROOM FOR YOUTH AGES 8 TO 14; STUDIOS FOR YOGA, DANCE, PILATES, PHYSICAL THERAPY, CHIROPRACTOR, ACUPUNCTURIST, AND MASSAGE THERAPY; RACQUET BALL COURTS; CARDIO AND STRENGTH TRAINING FACILITIES; AND OUTDOOR TENNIS COURTS AND BALL FIELDS. MORE THAN 75 GROUP FITNESS CLASSES ARE OFFERED EACH WEEK FOR ADULTS. IN ADDITION, A VARIETY OF CLASSES AND LESSONS ARE OFFERED TO CHILDREN OF ALL AGES THROUGHOUT THE YEAR INCLUDING RED CROSS CERTIFIED SWIMMING CLASSES.

Activity2.Description: CHILDREN AND YOUTH PROGRAM (UNDUPLICATED PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS 2,472, INCLUDES MEMBERS AND NON MEMBERS)THE JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER'S COMPREHENSIVE APPROACH TO CHILDREN AND YOUTH PROGRAMMING INCORPORATE SOCIAL, EDUCATIONAL, CULTURAL AND FITNESS PROGRAMMING INTO AFTER SCHOOL CARE AND SUMMER CAMPING EXPERIENCES. THE AFTER SCHOOL CARE PROGRAM AT THE JCC SERVES THE NEEDS OF FAMILIES WITH SCHOOL-AGED CHILDREN IN KINDERGARTEN THROUGH SIXTH GRADE. JCC'S AFTER SCHOOL PROGRAM IS A BRIDGE (GESHER) BETWEEN HOME AND SCHOOL, WITH AFTER SCHOOL ACTIVITIES AND CLASSES, RECREATION PROGRAMS, AND SCHOOL VACATION PROGRAMS.CAMP SISOL IS A VIBRANT DAY-CAMPING COMMUNITY, GROUNDED IN JEWISH VALUES AND CULTURE. CAMP SISOL HELPS CHILDREN AGE 5 THROUGH 15 DEVELOP CONFIDENCE, HAPPINESS, AND KINDNESS THROUGH AN INTEGRATED PROGRAM THAT BUILDS LIFELONG MEMORIES AND RESPECT FOR COMMUNITY. IN ADDITION, CAMP SISOL OFFERS CHILDREN WITH DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITIES THE OPPORTUNITY TO PARTICIPATE IN ITS PROGRAM IN AN INCLUSIVE SETTING. LOCATED ON 75 ROLLING ACRES IN HONEOYE FALLS, NY THE JCC PROVIDES BUSSING AND NUTRITIOUS MEALS FOR CHILDREN PARTICIPATING IN THIS FULL-DAY SUMMER PROGRAM. CAMP SENECA LAKE IS THE JCC'S OVERNIGHT CAMP SERVING CHILDREN BETWEEN THE AGES OF 8 AND 16 FOR MORE THAN 80 YEARS. LOCATED ON MORE THAN 200 ACRES ON SENECA LAKE IN WESTERN, NY, CSL IS COMMITTED TO PROVIDING A WHOLESOME JEWISH CAMP COMMUNITY DEDICATED TO DEVELOPING THE PHYSICAL, SOCIAL, AND EMOTIONAL IDENTITIES OF ITS CAMPERS. CAMPERS EXPERIENCE A BALANCE PROGRAM OF GROUP AND INDIVIDUAL ACTIVITIES LED BY A MATURE AND SKILLED STAFF. THIS IS ACCOMPLISHED WHILE PROVIDING CAMPERS AN EXCITING AND FUN-FILLED SUMMER IN A BEAUTIFUL LAKEFRONT SETTING, CREATING MEMORIES AND FRIENDSHIPS THAT WILL LAST A LIFETIME.IN ADDITION TO CAMP SISOL AND CAMP SENECA LAKE, THIS PAST YEAR THE JCC OFFERED ITS SUMMER DRAMA PROGRAM ON-STAGE FOR CHILDREN AGES 8 THROUGH 15 AND PREMIER SOCCER CAMP FOR CHILDREN AGE 7 TO 15. BOTH CAMPS OFFERED AN ALTERNATIVE TO TRADITIONAL, NATURE-BASED CAMPING PROGRAMS.

Activity3.Description: EARLY CHILDHOOD (UNDUPLICATED PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS 509, INCLUDES MEMBERS AND NON MEMBERS)THE JCC WOLK CHILDREN'S CENTER PROVIDES AN ACCREDITED FULL-DAY AND PART-TIME EARLY CHILDHOOD EXPERIENCE FOR CHLDREN BETWEEN THE AGES OF 8 WEEKS AND 5 YEARS. THE PROGRAM OFFERS A RICHLY VARIED CURRICULUM THAT ENCOURAGES INTELLECTUAL CURIOSITY, BUILDS SELF-CONFIDENCE. COMPLEMENTING OUR DAILY CORE PROGRAM, CHILDREN HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY TO PARTICIPATE IN A VARIETY OF ENRICHED PROGRAMMING, INCLUDING MUSIC, SCIENCE, PHYSICAL EDUCATION AND AQUATICS. FAMILIES FROM ALL BACKGROUNDS ENJOY CULTURAL, RECREATIONAL, SOCIAL, EDUCATIONAL AND JUDAIC PROGRAMS THROUGHOUT THE YEAR AT THE JCC. THE JCC IS COMMITTED TO EXPANDING AND ENRICHING THE LIVES OF ADULTS WITH DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITIES AND OFFERS A MYRIAD OF SOCIAL AND RECREATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES FOR INDIVIDUALS AND GROUPS. OUR PROGRAMS SERVE THE DEVELOPMENTALLY DISABILED IN A SETTING THAT REINFORCES AND PROMOTES INDEPENDENCE, SOCIAL INTEGRATION AND PRODUCTIVITY ON MULTIPLE LEVELS. ENABLING THOSE WITH DISABILITIES TO LIVE MORE FULLY IS A BROAD CONCEPT THAT ENCOURAGES AND EXTENDS A BALANCE OF PHYSICAL, INTELLECTUAL, EMOTIONAL, SOCIAL AND SPIRITUAL HEALTH THROUGHOUT A LIFETIME. TO THAT END, THE JCC OF ROCHESTER OFFERS CLASSES, ACTIVITIES, PROGRAMS, ARTISTIC ENDEAVORS AND CULTURAL EVENTS THAT PROVIDE A LONG LASTING AND POSITIVIE IMPACT ON THE LIVES OF THOSE WITH SPECIAL NEEDS.

ActivityOther.Description: CULTURAL ARTS AND THEATRE (22,700 VISITS/YEAR)JEWISH PROGRAMMING AT THE JCC REFLECTS OUR COMMUNITY'S VALUES. OUR LAY LEADER, VOLUNTEER AND STAFF SUPPORT ENSURES THAT RICH JEWISH CULTURAL PROGRAMS ARE DELIVERED TO OUR COMMUNITY EACH YEAR WITHOUT FAIL. THE JCC'S FEINBLOOM CENTER FOR THE ARTS CELEBRATES THE JEWISH STAGE, THE JEWISH BOOK, THE JEWISH FILM, YIDDISH, AND MANY JEWISH-RELATED MEDIA THROUGH OUR FEINBLOOM LIBRARY.THE AMES-AMZALAK ROCHESTER JEWISH FILM FESTIVAL IS THE LARGEST JEWISH CULTURAL EVEN IN WESTERN NEW YORK. EACH YEAR, THE FESIVAL SCREENS MORE THAN 15 FILMS OF JEWISH INTEREST AT BOTH THE HISTORIC DRYDEN THEATRE AT GEORGE EASTMAN HOUSE, AND THE LITTLE THEATRE IN THE HEART OF ROCHESTER'S CULTURAL DISTRICT. THE LANE DWORKIN JEWISH BOOK FESTIVAL HAS BEEN SHOWCASING JEWISH AUTHORS AND BOOKS OF JEWISH CONTENT SINCE 1993 AT THE JCC. EACH YEAR WE OFFER A MIXTURE OF LIGHT AND SERIOUS FARE, LOCAL AUTHORS, WELL-KNOWN FIGURES AND NOTABLE WRITERS. JCC CENTERSTAGE, SINCE 1977, HAS BEEN PROVIDING QUALITY ENTERTAINMENT AS THE RESIDENT THEATRE COMPANY OF THE JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER OF GREATER ROCHESTER. THIS PROFESSIONAL COMMUNITY THEATRE PRESENTS AN ANNUAL SUBSCRIPTION SERIES OF MUSICALS, COMEDIES AND DRAMAS IN THE BEAUTIFUL 288 SEATS HART THEATRE. CENTERSTAGE IS ALSO SPONSOR OF AN ANNUAL SUMMERSTAGE MUSICAL FOR HIGH SCHOOL AND COLLEGE STUDENTS AND AN ANNUAL SERIES OF READER THEATRE PRESENTATIONS. YIDDISH CULTURAL CENTER AT THE JCC IS THE MOST RECENT ADDITION TO JCC JEWISH CULTURAL ARTS PROGRAMMING. THE YIDDISH CULTURE CENTER AT THE JCC WAS ESTABLISHED TO ENCOURAGE THE REVIVAL OF THE YIDDISH LANGUAGE AS WELL AS YIDDISH CULTURE. THE BEAUTIFULLY DECORATED CENTER WAS MADE POSSIBLE THROUGH THE GENEROSITY OF DONORS PASSIONATE ABOUT KEEPING YIDDISH ALIVE AND WELL IN ROCHESTER. IT CONTAINS HUNDREDS OF YIDDISH BOOKS THAT HAVE BEEN DONATED THROUGHOUT THE YEARS. JCC MEMBERS AND MEMBERS FROM THE COMMUNITY MAY VISIT THE CENTER TO WATCH YIDDISH MOVIES, READ YIDDISH PERIODICALS (BOTH IN YIDDISH AND ENGLISH), HAVE ACCESS TO YIDDISH BOOKS, AND USE THE COMPUTER FOR RESEARCH ON YIDDISH SUBJECTS.THE FEINBLOOM LIBRARY IS A SPECIAL PLACE. IT IS A HUB FOR JEWISH LEARNING AT THE JCC. THE LIBRARY FEATURES AN EXTENSIVE COLLECTION OF BOOKS FOR JEWISH INTEREST, BOOKS BY JEWISH AUTHORS, LARGE PRINT BOOKS, PLUS A WIDE RANGE OR PERIODICALS, INCLUDING SUNDAY NEW YORK TIMES. IN ADDITION, THE LIBRARY IS HOME TO THE MORESS PEACE LIBRARY. ADULTS, SENIORS ADULTS, AND ADULTS WITH DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITIES (UNDUPLICATED PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS 13,310, INCLUDES MEMBERS AND NON MEMBERS)THE JEWISH COMMUNITY CENTER ADULT PROGRAM PROVIDES ADULTS WITH OPPORTUNITIES TO PARTICIPATE IN A SETTING THAT REINFORCES AND PROMOTES HEALTHY AGING ON MULTIPLE LEVELS IN A JEWISH ENVIRONMENT. HEALTHY AGING INVOLVES MORE THAN PHYSICAL HEALTH OR ABSENCE OF DISEASE. IT IS A BROAD CONCEPT THAT ENCOURAGES AND EXTENDS A BALANCE OF PHYSICAL, INTELLECTUAL, EMOTIONAL, SOCIAL AND SPIRITUAL HEALTH THROUGHOUT MATURE ADULTHOOD. THE JCC OF ROCHESTER OFFERS CLASSES, ACTIVITIES, PROGRAMS, ARTISTIC ENDEAVORS AND SPECIAL EVENTS DESIGNED FOR THE MATURE POPULATION AND SUPPORTS HEALTHY AGING INCLUDING EXERCISE AND WELLNESS PROGRAMS; ENTERTAINMENT, SOCIALS AND GUEST SPEAKERS AND CURRENT EVENT DISCUSSION GROUPS, ESCORTED TRAVEL CLUB; AFTERNOON MOVIES; INFORMAL SOCIALIZING; CARDS, MAHJONGG AND BOARD GAMES; AND HOLIDAY CELEBRATIONS.IN ADDITION, THE JCC SENIOR DEPARTMENT SERVES TO SUPPORT SENIORS TO ENABLE THEM TO LIVE LONGER INDEPENDENTLY IN THEIR OWN HOMES. THE JCC WORKS TOWARD THIS GOAL BY PROVIDING TRANSPORTATION SERVICES AND INFORMATION AND REFERRALS IN PARTNERSHIP WITH JEWISH FAMILY SERVICE.
